#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 1.26.1 Release Notes"
msgstr "NumPy 1.26.1 發行備註"

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:7
msgid ""
"NumPy 1.26.1 is a maintenance release that fixes bugs and regressions "
"discovered after the 1.26.0 release. In addition, it adds new functionality "
"for detecting BLAS and LAPACK when building from source. Highlights are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:11
msgid "Improved detection of BLAS and LAPACK libraries for meson builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:12
msgid "Pickle compatibility with the upcoming NumPy 2.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:14
msgid ""
"The 1.26.release series is the last planned minor release series before "
"NumPy 2.0. The Python versions supported by this release are 3.9-3.12."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:19
msgid "Build system changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:22
msgid "Improved BLAS/LAPACK detection and control"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:24
msgid ""
"Auto-detection for a number of BLAS and LAPACK is now implemented for Meson. "
"By default, the build system will try to detect MKL, Accelerate (on macOS "
">=13.3), OpenBLAS, FlexiBLAS, BLIS and reference BLAS/LAPACK. Support for "
"MKL was significantly improved, and support for FlexiBLAS was added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:29
msgid ""
"New command-line flags are available to further control the selection of the "
"BLAS and LAPACK libraries to build against."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:32
msgid ""
"To select a specific library, use the config-settings interface via ``pip`` "
"or ``pypa/build``. E.g., to select ``libblas``/``liblapack``, use::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:35
msgid ""
"$ pip install numpy -Csetup-args=-Dblas=blas -Csetup-args=-Dlapack=lapack\n"
"$ # OR\n"
"$ python -m build . -Csetup-args=-Dblas=blas -Csetup-args=-Dlapack=lapack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:39
msgid ""
"This works not only for the libraries named above, but for any library that "
"Meson is able to detect with the given name through ``pkg-config`` or CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:42
msgid ""
"Besides ``-Dblas`` and ``-Dlapack``, a number of other new flags are "
"available to control BLAS/LAPACK selection and behavior:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:45
msgid ""
"``-Dblas-order`` and ``-Dlapack-order``: a list of library names to search "
"for in order, overriding the default search order."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:47
msgid ""
"``-Duse-ilp64``: if set to ``true``, use ILP64 (64-bit integer) BLAS and "
"LAPACK. Note that with this release, ILP64 support has been extended to "
"include MKL and FlexiBLAS. OpenBLAS and Accelerate were supported in "
"previous releases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:51
msgid ""
"``-Dallow-noblas``: if set to ``true``, allow NumPy to build with its "
"internal (very slow) fallback routines instead of linking against an "
"external BLAS/LAPACK library. *The default for this flag may be changed to "
"``true`` in a future 1.26.x release, however for 1.26.1 we'd prefer to keep "
"it as ``false`` because if failures to detect an installed library are "
"happening, we'd like a bug report for that, so we can quickly assess whether "
"the new auto-detection machinery needs further improvements.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:58
msgid ""
"``-Dmkl-threading``: to select the threading layer for MKL. There are four "
"options: ``seq``, ``iomp``, ``gomp`` and ``tbb``. The default is ``auto``, "
"which selects from those four as appropriate given the version of MKL "
"selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:62
msgid ""
"``-Dblas-symbol-suffix``: manually select the symbol suffix to use for the "
"library - should only be needed for linking against libraries built in a non-"
"standard way."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:68
msgid "New features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:71
msgid "``numpy._core`` submodule stubs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.26.1-notes.rst:73
msgid ""
"``numpy._core`` submodule stubs were added to provide compatibility with "
"pickled arrays created using NumPy 2.0 when running Numpy 1.26."
msgstr ""

